# gen79: emergent rule induction. After each RULE assertion, kb_induce runs
# and any newly discovered implications are announced as "Induced: ...".
# The induction is statistical: implications hold where ALL known entities
# of one class are also in another (minimum 2 support).
# Setup: 3 dogs, 2 pets. Lassie is a dog but not a pet.
> rex is a dog
< Learned: dog(rex).
> fido is a dog
< Learned: dog(fido).
> lassie is a dog
< Learned: dog(lassie).
> rex is a pet
< Learned: pet(rex).
> fido is a pet
< Learned: pet(fido).
# Rule: every pet is a dog (true). No new inductions because
# the reverse (dog→pet) is false (lassie is a dog but not a pet).
> every pet is a dog
< Learned rule: dog(X) :- pet(X).
# Add a third category shared by rex and fido but NOT lassie.
> rex is a happy
< Learned: happy(rex).
> fido is a happy
< Learned: happy(fido).
# Rule: every pet is happy. Since all pets = rex, fido = all happy,
# induction finds bidirectional implications with happy.
> every pet is a happy
< Learned rule: happy(X) :- pet(X). Induced: dog(X) :- happy(X). pet(X) :- happy(X).
